You can use Formik&#39;s built in ```setFieldValue``` function to define your own change handler for the input which will set the number value directly:

```
           &lt;InputNumber
                    id={count}
                    name={count}
                    type={&quot;number&quot;}
                    onChange={v =&gt; {
                      props.setFieldValue(count, v);
                    }}
                    onBlur={props.handleBlur}
                    defaultValue={props.initialValues[count]}
                    placeholder=&quot;Count&quot;
                  /&gt;
```

According to [the docs](https://jaredpalmer.com/formik/docs/api/formik) it also has a third boolean argument to determine whether or not to run validation.  So passing in ```true``` after ```v``` should trigger validation if ```validateOnChange``` is enabled on the main ```Formik``` component.

