You can set the **&quot;div box&quot;** to a **`boolean` value** &amp; then create a method which toggles the **`boolean`** between **`true/false`** like so:

**Template:**
```
&lt;div id=&quot;app&quot;&gt;
  &lt;transition name=&quot;fade&quot; mode=&quot;out-in&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div v-if=&quot;boxA&quot; key=&quot;boxA&quot;&gt;Div A&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div v-else key=&quot;boxB&quot;&gt;Div B&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/transition&gt;
  
  &lt;button @click=&quot;toggleBoxes&quot;&gt;Toggle div boxes!&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
```

**JavaScript:**
```
new Vue({
  el: &quot;#app&quot;,
  data: {
    boxA: true
  },
  methods: {
  	toggleBoxes() {
    	this.boxA = !this.boxA;
    }
  }
})
```
**Edit:**

As for the **`&lt;transition&gt;`**, when toggling between elements that have the same tag name, you must tell **[Vue](https://vuejs.org/)** that they are distinct elements by giving them **unique key attributes** (**`key=&#39;&lt;uniqueKey&gt;&#39;`**) to the **tag elements**, you can read about it **[here](https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/transitions.html#Transitioning-Between-Elements)**.

You can check this **[working code sample](https://jsfiddle.net/qaxbchrt/1/)**.

However, if you still want to have **two buttons** to toggle the **`&lt;div&gt;`**, check **[this code](https://jsfiddle.net/mercenariomode/yngp1hea/)** instead.

Furthermore, I highly suggest you to read the **official documentation** on **[Conditional Rendering with Vuejs](https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/conditional.html)**.

