Grid Items just setup your layout.

They don&#39;t actually display anything.  The MUI display option is for hiding specific elements.

Try this:

```
function CRUDView() {
  return (
    &lt;Grid
      container
      spacing={1}
      direction=&quot;row&quot;
      justify=&quot;center&quot;
      alignItems=&quot;center&quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;Grid item xs={12} lg={6}&gt;
        &lt;span&gt;XX&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/Grid&gt;
      //removed from the below Grid Item
      &lt;Grid item xs={12} lg={6}&gt;
        &lt;span display={{ xs: &quot;none&quot;, lg: &quot;block&quot; }}&gt;YY&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/Grid&gt;
    &lt;/Grid&gt;
  );
}
```

That will hide the individual `span` element even though the grid is still there.

The [style functions](https://material-ui.com/system/basics/) are not automatically supported by the `Grid` component.

The easiest way to leverage the style functions is to use the [Box component](https://material-ui.com/components/box/). The `Box` component makes all of the style functions (such as [display](https://material-ui.com/system/display/)) available. The `Box` component has a [component prop](https://material-ui.com/components/box/#api) (which defaults to `div`) to support using `Box` to add style functions to another component.

The `Grid` component similarly has a [component prop](https://material-ui.com/api/grid/#props), so you can either have a `Grid` that delegates its rendering to a `Box` or a `Box` that delegates to a `Grid`.

The example below (based on your code) shows both ways of using `Box` and `Grid` together.

```
import React from &quot;react&quot;;
import ReactDOM from &quot;react-dom&quot;;

import Grid from &quot;@material-ui/core/Grid&quot;;
import Box from &quot;@material-ui/core/Box&quot;;
import { makeStyles } from &quot;@material-ui/core/styles&quot;;

const useStyles = makeStyles({
  gridItem: {
    border: &quot;1px solid red&quot;
  }
});

function App() {
  const classes = useStyles();
  return (
    &lt;Grid
      container
      spacing={1}
      direction=&quot;row&quot;
      justify=&quot;center&quot;
      alignItems=&quot;center&quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;Grid className={classes.gridItem} item xs={12} lg={6}&gt;
        &lt;span&gt;XX&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/Grid&gt;
      &lt;Box
        component={Grid}
        className={classes.gridItem}
        item
        xs={3}
        display={{ xs: &quot;none&quot;, lg: &quot;block&quot; }}
      &gt;
        &lt;span&gt;YY&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/Box&gt;
      &lt;Grid
        component={Box}
        className={classes.gridItem}
        item
        xs={3}
        display={{ xs: &quot;none&quot;, lg: &quot;block&quot; }}
      &gt;
        &lt;span&gt;ZZ&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;/Grid&gt;
    &lt;/Grid&gt;
  );
}

const rootElement = document.getElementById(&quot;root&quot;);
ReactDOM.render(&lt;App /&gt;, rootElement);
```

